{
  "stem": "23278.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My actual work was my vacation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with that I managed to publish more than the whole faculty together in seven years, but they didn't give me tenure because I was a woman.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But anyway, I had seven good years where my children became accustomed to America in a smaller town, where a lot of French was spoken, with the Canadian-- and where they went to private school, because the public school were horrible.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when they took-- and that it's one of my pet peeve with the system in America-- they took English right away, and they took French as second language.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When they entered school in September, they didn't know any English.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "By the time Christmas came, they spoke fluently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "At the end of the year, they knew more than the others, because their schooling was more advanced in Europe than here.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they took French as second language to learn the grammar, the spelling, and everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that's what we should do with our Spanish-speaking people, instead of putting them in a cultural ghetto as we do.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was '42, '43, because we-- we had no food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know, it kind of diminishes your spirit, you could say, where our aim of the day was to find a few potatoes, for instance.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had little bags that had been sewn out of towels where we put our bread so my father would not eat our bread by mistake, or we wouldn't eat a crumb of somebody else.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The bread was the equivalent of two slices of pumpernickel for the day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But butter ration was like one square of butter a month for four people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was working in the same thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother too.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
